  "local_port": 34250,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which are the best CBSE schools in Hyderabad?",
  "response": "Choosing the \"best\" CBSE (Central Board of Secondary Education) school in Hyderabad can depend on various factors such as location, facilities, faculty quality, academic performance, extracurricular activities, and individual student needs. However, several CBSE schools in Hyderabad are renowned for their excellence in education and holistic development. Here are some of the top CBSE schools in Hyderabad:\n\n1. **Delhi Public School (DPS), Hyderabad**\n   - **Locations:** Multiple branches including Kondapur, Gachibowli, and Banjara Hills.\n   - **Highlights:** Part of the prestigious DPS Society, known for high academic standards, excellent infrastructure, and a wide range of extracurricular activities.\n\n2. **Kendriya Vidyalaya (KV), Various Locations**\n   - **Locations:** Numerous branches across Hyderabad.\n   - **Highlights:** Central government schools offering quality education, affordable fees, and a balanced curriculum focusing on academics and co-curricular activities.\n\n3. **Bharatiya Vidya Bhavan's Public School, Banjara Hills**\n   - **Highlights:** Emphasizes Indian culture and values alongside a robust academic curriculum, well-equipped facilities, and experienced faculty.\n\n4. **Oakridge International School, Madhapur**\n   - **Highlights:** Although Oakridge offers multiple curricula, its CBSE stream is highly regarded for academic rigor, modern infrastructure, and a focus on all-round development.\n\n5. **Glendale Academy, Banjara Hills**\n   - **Highlights:** Known for its strong academic performance, excellent teacher-student ratio, and comprehensive extracurricular programs.\n\n6. **Chirec International School, Kondapur**\n   - **Highlights:** Offers a rigorous CBSE curriculum with state-of-the-art facilities, emphasis on technology integration, and various co-curricular activities.\n\n7. **Saraswati Vidya Bhavan, Gowhershwar**\n   - **Highlights:** Focuses on academic excellence, cultural activities, and sports, with well-qualified teachers and good infrastructure.\n\n8. **Indus International School, Banjara Hills**\n   - **Highlights:** While primarily known for its international curriculum, Indus also offers a CBSE stream that is praised for its quality education and comprehensive facilities.\n\n9. **Sri Chaitanya Techno School, Himayatnagar**\n   - **Highlights:** Part of the renowned Sri Chaitanya group, it offers strong academic support, especially in science and mathematics, along with extracurricular activities.\n\n10. **Lotus Valley International School, Kapra**\n    - **Highlights:** Known for its student-centric approach, modern facilities, and emphasis on both academics and extracurricular development.\n\n**Factors to Consider When Choosing a School:**\n- **Academic Performance:** Look into the school's board examination results and overall academic reputation.\n- **Infrastructure:** Check for adequate classrooms, laboratories, libraries, sports facilities, and technology integration.\n- **Faculty:** Experienced and qualified teachers can significantly impact your child\u2019s learning experience.\n- **Extracurricular Activities:** A school that offers a variety of activities helps in the overall development of students.\n- **Location and Accessibility:** Proximity to your residence can reduce commute time and stress.\n- **Fee Structure:** Ensure that the school's fees align with your budget while offering good value.\n\n**Conclusion:**\nIt's essential to visit the schools, interact with faculty and administration, and understand their teaching philosophies before making a decision. What works best for one student may not necessarily be the best for another, so consider your child\u2019s unique needs and preferences when selecting a school.",
